## Web / Dashboard Interaction Standards

### Rule IXD-006: Navigation and Information Architecture

- Primary navigation (top-level sections): max 7 items
- Secondary navigation: sidebar with clear section headings
- Current location always visible (breadcrumb or highlighted nav item)
- Every page reachable within 3 clicks from the home page
- URLs are stable, descriptive, and bookmarkable

### Rule IXD-007: Forms and Data Entry

| Element | Requirement |
|---------|-------------|
| Required fields | Marked with visible indicator (not just red color); explained in legend |
| Optional fields | No marker, or explicit "(optional)" label |
| Validation | Inline, on field blur (not only on submit); show validation state clearly |
| Error placement | Directly beneath the field that caused the error |
| Error messages | State what is wrong and how to fix it |
| Success confirmation | Shown after form submission; includes what was changed |
| Destructive actions | Require confirmation dialog with explicit description of consequence |

### Rule IXD-008: State Communication

Users must always know the system state. Every possible state must be designed:

| State | Design Requirement |
|-------|-------------------|
| Loading | Skeleton screen or spinner; never blank content area |
| Empty | Illustrated or textual empty state with call to action |
| Error | Friendly error message with recovery option |
| Success | Confirmation message; auto-dismiss for low-stakes actions |
| Partial / warning | Inline badge or banner; not a blocking modal |
| Offline | Clear indicator; queue or disable actions that require connectivity |

### Rule IXD-009: Keyboard and Accessibility

- All interactive elements reachable via keyboard (Tab, Shift+Tab)
- Focus order follows visual reading order (top to bottom, left to right)
- Focus ring always visible (never hidden with `outline: none` without replacement)
- All images have `alt` text; decorative images have empty `alt=""`
- Form fields have associated `<label>` elements (not `placeholder` as substitute)
- Color is never the sole differentiator for information (also use icons, text, patterns)
- Minimum contrast ratio: 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- Interactive elements minimum touch target: 44×44px

### Rule IXD-010: Responsive Design

- Mobile-first approach: design smallest viewport first, then expand
- Breakpoints documented in design system (if web system has one)
- Critical workflows must be completable on mobile without horizontal scrolling
- Tables on mobile: use horizontal scroll container or responsive layout (not truncation without disclosure)

