## Cross-Interface Standards

### Rule IXD-014: Terminology Consistency Across Interfaces

The same concept must use the same term in every interface (CLI, Web, API, docs). When a discrepancy is found, refer to the architecture's glossary / Vision Document Section 7 for the canonical term.

Create or update `docs/GLOSSARY.md` when new user-visible terms are introduced.

### Rule IXD-015: Interaction Flows Documentation Requirement

Every significant user interaction flow must be documented in the Interaction Design document (`.cursor/templates/ux/INTERACTION-DESIGN-TEMPLATE.md`). A "significant flow" is any that:

- Involves more than 2 steps to complete
- Has non-obvious error states
- Differs from conventional patterns for the interface type
- Represents a primary user workflow from the Vision Document

